olar eclipses in modern times to reveal the profound effects these cosmic events have had on human history. Colored by his own experiences—Aveni has witnessed eight total solar eclipses in his lifetime—his account of astronomy’s most storied phenomenon will enthrall anyone who has looked up at the sky with wonder.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 27. Okt 2021) 0aEclipses. 0aSolar eclipses. 7aSCIENCE / Astronomy.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2017z978311063898140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300227574423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300227574/original  a978-3-11-063898-1  Yale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2017b2017  aGBV-deGruyter-alles